# White-label page titles (browser tabs)

Client portals must never show "KaiMentors" in the browser tab. Page body can be portal-branded while the tab still leaks if metadata is wrong.

## Root cause pattern

`app/layout.tsx` sets `title.template: "%s | KaiMentors"`. Any page that sets `title: "My Page"` as a plain string still becomes `"My Page | KaiMentors"`.

## Required pattern

Use `portalTitle()` from `@/lib/metadata` for every client-facing route:

```typescript
import { portalTitle } from "@/lib/metadata";

export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return portalTitle("Join PASII"); // → absolute title, no KaiMentors suffix
}
```

Never use plain `title: "..."` on routes reachable by students or mentors on custom domains.

## Routes that need explicit metadata

These are served **outside** `domain-sites/layout.tsx` and `student/layout.tsx` — easy to miss:

- `app/dashboard/**` — async `generateMetadata` in `dashboard/layout.tsx` via `getMentorWorkspace()`
- `app/join/workspace/[token]/page.tsx` — resolve portal from `invite_token`
- `app/domain-sites/[hostname]/login/page.tsx` — portal name from hostname

Any **new** route served natively on custom domains (middleware pass-through) must get the same treatment.

## Allowed KaiMentors branding

- `app/layout.tsx` (platform root)
- `app/admin/**`
- `app/login/page.tsx` (platform mentor login)
- `app/page.tsx` (platform marketing homepage)

## Before marking a white-label mission complete

Verify tab titles (not just page copy) on a custom domain:

- `/join/workspace/{token}` → `Join {portal_name}`
- `/dashboard` → `{portal_name}`
- `/login` → `Sign In · {portal_name}` or `{portal_name}`

**Fail if the tab contains "KaiMentors" on any client portal.**
